      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Warm the treacle, rub in the butter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 220°C fan. ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "Warm the treacle and milk together",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp99dsg90000t4v4ic2uw9h1"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " in a small pan over a low heat until the treacle loosens and the liquid is pourable. Set aside to cool to lukewarm. Sift the {{self-raising-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, {{mixed-spice}} and {{cinnamon-ground}} into a bowl. Rub in the {{unsalted-butter}} until the mixture looks like coarse breadcrumbs. Stir in the {{soft-brown-sugar}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bring together and cut",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the warm treacle-and-milk mixture into the flour all at once. Mix with a palette knife in figure-of-eight strokes until the dough comes together. The dough should look soft and a little tacky; if it is too dry add another tablespoon of milk. Tip onto a floured surface and pat to a 3 cm slab. Cut twelve rounds with a floured 5 cm cutter.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 12 to 14 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Set on a lined baking tray. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes; the tops should be deep mahogany (the treacle colours them quickly) and the sides should sound hollow when tapped. Cool on a rack 5 minutes before splitting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
